    "body": "> Your suggestion of namespacing `phase0.fast.processBlock` would remove the need to import from deep inside lib which was the main driver behind this issue. The difference between both solutions is to separate code inside the same package or in different packages. I don't have a strong opinion on either direction and would love to know your pros and cons of each path\r\n\r\nI guess biggest reason is that it would be easier to import because if we have phase0 namespace in both packages everywhere you use both original utilities and fast stuff you would have to manually rename import (`import {phase0 as phase0Fast}` or something).\r\n\r\n",
